/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  data/groupEstimative/ -- the group-contribution ESTIMATION lake
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

WHAT THIS TIER IS
  A PRE-CURATION staging lake of compounds whose identity, molecular groups,
  and pure-component properties were ESTIMATED by group contribution.  It is
  NOT reviewed reference data.  It exists to ORGANISE and FEED curation:
  consolidate one authoritative name + one group decomposition + a first-pass
  property set per compound, so a human can promote selected records upward.

  COVALENT SINGLE MOLECULES ONLY.
    components/  -- single-molecule compounds (~28.5k).  Audit-clean,
                    VLE-self-consistent, loadable, Joback-tiered.

  SALTS ARE NOT JOBACK-ESTIMATED -- BUT THEY ARE NOT THROWN AWAY.
    A salt is a perfectly valid Choupo component -- just NOT a Joback one.
    See data/standards/components/NaCl.dat: it carries identity + MW +
    `nonvolatile true` + `dissociatesTo { Na 1; Cl 1; }`, its formation lives
    PER ION, and its activity is Pitzer/eNRTL.  What a salt must NEVER have is
    a Joback MOLECULAR estimate: group contribution fragments a COVALENT
    structure and refers to the ideal gas, and a salt (an ion pair via proton
    transfer) has no single molecular Tc/Pc/Cp and must never route through the
    ideal-gas reference.

    So the ~116 detected salt entries leave the Joback lake but stay in the
    project in their proper form, under `salts/`: each carries identity + MW +
    `nonvolatile true` + a van't Hoff `dissociation` + a `dissociatesTo` map --
    the NaCl.dat shape -- and NO Joback numbers.  `dissociatesTo` is filled as a
    verifiable DRAFT where the constituents parse cleanly from the name (~39),
    and left as an explicit TODO where they do not (~77) -- auto-deriving it is
    unreliable (the split collides with commas inside the chemical name), so
    that last mile is a per-salt curation act, exactly as NaCl was.  The
    identity index is `salts-for-electrolyte-curation.csv`.
    Contents:  components/ (single covalent molecules) + salts/ (electrolyte form).

  Promotion path:   groupEstimative/  --(human review + PRIMARY citation)-->
                    data/proposed/  --(committee)-->  data/standards/
  Trust order:      groupEstimative  <  proposed  <  standards  <  case-local

THE ENGINE DOES NOT READ THIS TIER.
  No solver, no ThermoPackageBuilder, no Database lookup consumes this folder.
  It is a curation input only.  A compound becomes engine-visible ONLY when a
  human promotes it into proposed/ or standards/ as a cited .dat.

EVERY NUMBER IS AN ESTIMATE (the warning travels with the data).
  Anchors (Tb, Tc, Pc, Vc, Tm, Cp_ig, dHf, dGf, Hvap, Hfus): Joback & Reid 1987
  group contribution.  omega: Lee-Kesler corresponding states from (Tb,Tc,Pc).
  Typical AAD: Tb ~10%, Tc ~11%, Pc ~11%; WORSE for small molecules and
  hydrogen-bonders.  Groups (UNIFAC/Dortmund/PSRK): DDBST published assignments.
  See SOURCES.md for provenance + licences.

THREE ORTHOGONAL AXES (ratified by the professors' forum; do not conflate)
  A  role        -- PHASE behaviour (volatile/nonvolatile/solute).  Lives on
                    the component .dat already; NOT decided here.
  B  stability   -- INTRINSIC nature: stable vs reactiveIntermediate (radical).
                    DERIVED here (RDKit radical-electron screen + a curated
                    allowlist of stable inorganic radicals: NO, NO2, O2, ...).
                    reactiveIntermediate species are KINETICS-ONLY -- they must
                    never enter a flash / VLE / distillation (engine refusal is
                    a separate, pending change; see NOTE).
  C  representation (lumped/dissociated ion) -- chosen by the propertyPackage,
                    NEVER stored on the substance.  Untouched here.

COLUMNS (all derived; nothing hand-authored)
  identity:   name, CAS, formula, InChIKey, charge
  axis B:     stability (stable|reactiveIntermediate)
  view:       thermo_class (molecular|radical|electrolyte|gas),
              models_supported, unifac_vocab_ok
  groups:     unifac, modfac, psrk  ("subgroupId:count ..."; DDBST numbering)
  estimates:  MW, Tb, Tc, Pc, Vc, omega, Tm, dHf/dGf(ig), Hvap(Tb), Hfus,
              Cpig_{a,b,c,d}, anchor_method, omega_method

  unifac_vocab_ok = yes when every subgroup maps to a name present in
  data/standards/unifac/groups.dat (~21k of 28.8k).  The remainder need a
  subgroup-name reconciliation before they can feed Choupo's UNIFAC.

CURRENT CONTENTS (this build)
  28823 compounds | stability: 28661 stable, 162 reactiveIntermediate
  thermo_class: 28661 molecular, 162 radical | unifac_vocab_ok(yes): 20996
  (The DDBST harvest is all neutral molecules with groups; ions/light gases
   are absent here -- they arrive from other sources with their own models.)

ENFORCEMENT
  bin/curate/check_groups.py cross-references a component tree against this
  prelist and reports any molecular, neutral, stable, vocab-OK compound that
  is MISSING its `groups { unifac (...) }` block.  --strict exits 1 (curation
  gate).  It is a standalone tool and is NOT wired into bin/runTests yet.

